'27:26': [
{sup:"1a", word:"scourged", vrefs:"Isa. 53:5; Matt. 20:19; 1&nbsp;Pet. 2:24", lines:["This utterly exposed the darkness and injustice of politics! This injustice fulfilled {Isa53:5|Isa. 53:5}, {Isa53:8|8}."]},
{sup:2, word:"crucified", lines:["The Jewish death penalty was carried out by stoning ({Lev20:2|Lev. 20:2}, {Lev20:27|27}; {Lev24:14|24:14}; {Deu13:10|Deut. 13:10}; {Deu17:5|17:5}). Crucifixion was a heathen practice ({Ezr6:11|Ezra 6:11}) adopted by the Romans for the execution of slaves and heinous criminals only. The Lord Jesus&rsquo; being crucified was a fulfillment not only of the Old Testament prophecies ({Deu21:23|Deut. 21:23}; {Gal3:13|Gal. 3:13}; {Num21:8|Num. 21:8}-{Num21:9|9}) but also of the Lord&rsquo;s word concerning how He would die ({Joh3:14|John 3:14}; {Joh8:28|8:28}; {Joh12:32|12:32}). These could not have been fulfilled by stoning. See {Joh18:32^1|note 32<sup>1</sup>} in {Joh18|John 18}."]},
],
